PrecisRegulations Amending the FEDERAL REAL PROPERTY REGULATIONS to the extent that easement or rights-of-way may be granted for a consideration consisting of the periodic payment of a specified fee, surplus land may be transferred to Crown corporations whose activities are restricted to dealings in real estate, and that a retrocession of land or an interest therein may be effected by an instrument other than an Order in Council.
